data.description:
When I started working for my company, I was tasked with recording all users activity in our redactor - click, move, keypress, everything.
And i had to create algorithm which had to understand which changes there were in string after user action and write their down like object with properties:
index - index where started change string,
add - symbols which was added,
deleted - symbols which was deleted.
User could copy and paste text in editor that's why you have to handle cases with added more than 1 symbol
for example:

findDifferent('Hello, world!', 'Harry, world!') => {
  index: 1,
  addedText: "arry",
  deletedText: "ello"
}

User click mouse from position 1 and select text 'ello' and paste text arry.

that's why function have to return {index: 1, addedText: "arry", deletedText: "ello"}

findDifferent('It is hard task', 'It is easy task') => {
  index: 6,
  addedText: "easy",
  deletedText: "hard"
};

findDifferent('My first task', 'My second task for you') => {
  index: 3, 
  addedText: "second task for you", 
  deletedText: "first task"
}

if two string are the same then function has to return false.

findDifferent('The same text', 'The same text') => false;
